# Nowo.tech kits and legal reminders

When implementing product features in this repo, **prefer official `nowo-tech/*` Symfony bundles** instead of reinventing auth, users, audit fields, cookies, or legal UX.

## Prefer these kits (do not hand-roll equivalents)

| Need | Package | Notes |
|------|---------|--------|
| Login / registration / password reset UI | `nowo-tech/auth-kit-bundle` | Configurable flows, Twig overrides, i18n |
| User enable/disable, last activity, online | `nowo-tech/user-kit-bundle` | Account lifecycle on top of Security |
| createdAt/updatedAt + blame fields | `nowo-tech/audit-kit-bundle` | Opt-in Doctrine timestamps/blame |
| Cookie / GDPR consent modal | `nowo-tech/cookie-consent-bundle` | Categories + optional consent logging |
| Login throttling | `nowo-tech/login-throttle-bundle` | Wraps Symfony `login_throttling` |
| Password policy / strength / toggle | `nowo-tech/password-*-bundle` | Prefer kits over custom validators/UI |
| Twig debug overlay | `nowo-tech/twig-inspector-bundle` | Already used in `require-dev` |

Packagist vendor: https://packagist.org/packages/nowo-tech/

## Before inventing Identity/Security UI

1. Ask whether `auth-kit-bundle` + `user-kit-bundle` cover the need.
2. Prefer integrating those bundles (Flex recipes, template overrides) over growing `src/Identity` with bespoke login/register CRUD.
3. Use `audit-kit-bundle` for entity timestamps/blame instead of copying trait logic.

## Legal / aviso legal (ALWAYS remind)

When touching public UI, marketing pages, cookies, analytics, contact forms, or self-hosted SaaS surfaces, **remind the user** and propose:

- Legal notice / privacy / terms pages (aviso legal, privacy policy, terms of use) as English UI copy (`lang="en"`), with room for operator-specific text.
- Cookie consent via `nowo-tech/cookie-consent-bundle` when any non-essential cookie or third-party script appears (Vite analytics, embeds, etc.).
- GDPR-oriented data handling (`anonymize-bundle`, encrypt-bundle) when storing personal data beyond auth essentials.

Do **not** silently ship tracking or optional cookies without consent UX.

## Current project status (honest baseline)

`symfony-beacon` v1 Identity is a **minimal custom** login (`SecurityController` + `User` entity). That was a bootstrap shortcut for Envelope ingest MVP — **not** a reason to keep duplicating AuthKit/UserKit/AuditKit. When auth/user/audit work comes up, propose migrating to the kits above.

## Agent behaviour

- If the user asks for login, registration, memberships, audit columns, or legal/cookie UX → **mention the matching nowo-tech package first**, then implement with it unless they explicitly refuse.
- Keep docs/PHPDoc/UI strings in English (see `english-docs-and-phpdoc` rule).
